description: Deadpool is a terrorist?! That’s how Captain America sees it, but Cap doesn’t know there currently are two Deadpools in NYC--one who’s totally evil and one…well, one who’s not quite as bad. How will our dubious hero clear his name, get Captain America to not despise him, defeat the most formidable enemy he’s ever faced…oh, and evade capture by international law enforcement? Uh, who said he does?
name: Evil Deadpool, Part Four: Just Me, Baby

description: THE DEATH OF AN AVENGER. The Young Avengers find themselves on the wrong side of the Scarlet Witch's reality-altering powers in their final battle against the combined forces of THE AVENGERS and THE X-MEN. In this penultimate issue of the epic maxi-series, the Young Avengers have no one to turn to except each other as they are forced to fight their lifelong heroes, to the death. Find out who lives and who dies.

John Carter learns the shocking truth about the therns, the mysterious sect of priests who control the worship of Issus, the goddess of all Mars. He and Tars Tarkas, the greatest warrior of the green Martians, will have to battle their way through the hellish labyrinth of the therns' temples before they can tell anyone about their discovery. Fortunately for them, they'll have the help of Thuvia, Princess of Ptarth. But even if they free themselves from the temples, they'll have another, even more deadly threat to contend with: an ancient terror from Mars's larger moon...
name: Gods of Mars, Part 2, The Black Pirates

description: It includes stories of: Neura, Anaximandro, los Looser and Sor Rita
name: Noche de Paz - Aberración fuerte al espíritu Falso - Los looser

person_credits.name: Karmao

description: While Princess Kahm and Tetsuya, her human consort, struggle to survive the devastated Germany, the Imperial Fleet of the Santovasku Empire warps into orbit--led by the ruthless beast-man, Commander Geobaldi, Earth is already reeling, and the invasion has just begun!

It's been a bad day for alien royalty! While flying over war-ravaged Germany, Princess Kahm is shot down, captured, tied up, beaten, stripped naked--and then things get bad! Forty pages of nonstop action and excitement!

The invading Santovasku Empire turns its sights on Europe, sending in hordes of their "combat monsters" to battle the European and Soviet defenders! All looks lost for the forces of Earth, but the Santovasku have forgotten an important lesson from their distant past, and their over-confidence may lead to their doom!

More of the best manga from Japan! Princess Kahm takes Tetsuya, her reluctant Earthly lover, to her massive flagship where he discovers the history of the galaxy-spannings Santovaksu Empire, and learns that to Kahm's people, the human race are "insects" that must be exterminated!
In this issue the destinies of Kahm's living battle cruiser and of Japan itself are fatally linked, while Kahm's personal vendetta with Tetsuya turns into a more complex entanglement.

The alien Princess Kahm comes to Earth to regain her sword and to challenge our hero, the befuddled reporter Tetsuya, to a duel to the death! Meanwhile, the forces of the Earth continue their struggle against the otherwordly invaders--pitting a nuclear armed space shuttle against one of the aliens battle cruisers!
